        <section id="classroom">
            <h1>Simba Classroom (Infant)</h1>
            <p>The Simba classroom is designed for our youngest learners. We provide a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment to support their rapid growth and development.</p>

            <h2>Curriculum Agenda</h2>
            <p>Our infant curriculum focuses on key developmental milestones, including:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Sensory Exploration:</strong> Activities that engage their senses of touch, sight, and hearing.</li>
                <li><strong>Gross Motor Skills:</strong> Tummy time, reaching for toys, and supported sitting to build strength and coordination.</li>
                <li><strong>Cognitive Development:</strong> Responding to vocalizations, peek-a-boo, and object permanence games.</li>
                <li><strong>Language Skills:</strong> Reading books, singing songs, and engaging in responsive conversations to encourage early communication.</li>
                <li><strong>Social-Emotional Connections:</strong> Building secure attachments through consistent, loving care and routines.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Daily Schedule</h2>
            <p>The daily schedule for our infant and toddler classrooms is designed to be flexible and responsive to the children's individual needs.</p>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Time</th>
                        <th>Activity</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
